title: 820-02020 no power, PPBUS low
message:
Remove F5200 and check C5250 voltage.

Compare diode mode readings with good board.
Or use reference table:
[URL unfurl="true"]https://openboarddata.org/?a=showboardsolutions&bpath=laptops/apple/820-02020[/URL]

message:
Hi!

Also, I have shortage on PP3v8_AON, 8 ohm in both sides on L5800/L5820/L5840 or C5890/C5891/C5892/C5893 and C5894
I had injected 3 volts on C5890 and saw that U7700 got hotter ...

What do you think ? I must changed the U7700? It is PMIC APL1097

title: 820-02020 no power, PPBUS low
message:
You should change it.
Once removed, check if diode mode reading goes high enough.

BTW, PMUs from 14" and 16" M1 are interchangeable.
